    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-02-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="107" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                <head>No. 107.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lowell</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-02-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 24, 1882</date>.
                            (Received March 13.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 322.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                        two instructions Nos. 316 and 317 of the 10th instant, in relation to the
                        arrest and imprisonment of American citizens by the British Government; the
                        first in regard to the case of Mr. McSweeny, and the second, requesting me
                        to submit a full and accurate report upon the general subject, in obedience
                        to a resolution of the House of Representatives.</p>
                <p>I beg to say in reply that I have ordered copies to be made of such parts of
                        my correspondence respecting these matters as have not already been
                        transmitted to the Department of State, and that I shall forward such copies
                        to you so soon as they shall be finished, with such other information as I
                        may have obtained.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. E. LOWELL.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
